 as well as the history of Chanka ethnicity, the nature of Spanish colonialism, and the changing nature of Chanka politics and kinship from the fifteenth to the eighteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChanca IndiansxCrimes againstxHistoryxPeruxPampachiri. 0aChanca IndiansxCrimes againstzPeruzPampachirixHistory. 0aChanca IndiansxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311074524540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271077635?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271077635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271077635/original  a978-3-11-074524-5  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK